95 0 obj
<< /DA (/CourierStd 10.00 Tf 0 g) /F 68 /FT /Tx /Ff 8388609 /MK << >> /P 21 0 R /Parent 42 0 R /Q 0 /Rect [ 553.558 129.676 574.73 155.188 ] /StructParent 5 /Subtype /Widget /T <feff0052006500610064004f006e006c0079005f0046004c0044005b0030005d> /TU (We are writing to you because we believe you may have recent self-employment work activity and we need to know more about this work activity.  One of Social Security's top priorities is to support the efforts of applicants and beneficiaries with disabilities who are or who want to work.  The Social Security Disability Insurance \(S S D I\) and Supplemental Security Income \(S S I\) programs include several employment support provisions commonly referred to as work incentives, or special rules that help you to receive, or continue to receive benefits even if you are working. We need more information to see if any of these incentives apply to you. If you are just now applying for disability benefits, the information you provide helps us decide if you can receive benefits. If you are currently receiving disability benefits, the information you provide helps us decide if your benefits can continue. ) /Type /Annot >>
endobj
96 0 obj
<< /DA (/MyriadPro-Regular 10.00 Tf 0 g) /F 68 /FT /Tx /Ff 1 /MK << >> /P 22 0 R /Parent 43 0 R /Q 0 /Rect [ 542.586 492.857 572.916 512.699 ] /StructParent 7 /Subtype /Widget /T <feff0052006500610064004f006e006c00790031005f0046004c0044005b0030005d> /TU (Page 2 of 10. Information about Work and Earnings  Our records show that you may have self-employment income.  Common types of self-employment include: \200  Owning your own business, Sole Proprietorship/Corporation. \200  Owning a business with another person, Business Partnership. \200  Independent Contractor. \200  Freelancing for another business. \200  Gig Work, such as: bullet  Ride share driving services\rbullet Food delivery services\rbullet Internet content creator/influencer bullet   Musicians/Photographer/Artists bullet  Any job for which one receives form 10 99-N E C instead of form W 2 for I R S tax filing purposes.) /Type /Annot >>
endobj
97 0 obj
<< /DA (/CourierStd 10.00 Tf 0 g) /F 4 /FT /Tx /Ff 8388608 /MK << >> /P 22 0 R /Parent 43 0 R /Q 1 /Rect [ 52.464 185.12 313.503 205.37 ] /StructParent 8 /Subtype /Widget /T <feff0045006d0070006c006f0079006500720031005f0046004c0044005b0030005d> /TU (The information we ask for includes: \200 Self-Employment History: This includes the dates you worked, net earnings from self-employment, and any pay you received working as an independent contractor for another person or company \(e.g., driver, delivery, consulting, etc.\). \200  Special Self-employment Conditions: If you receive free help in your business, we may be able to deduct the reasonable value of that help from your net income. Also, if another person, agency or business provides items or services to you, free of charge, we may be able to deduct the reasonable value of those items or services from your net income. \200  Work Expenses related to your disability: If you are self-employed and have a disability, you may need certain items or services to assist you \(e.g., co-pays for prescription drugs, medical device expenses, special transportation, counseling fees, expenses related to a service animal, etc.\) Note: Do not include anything that you will include as a business expense on your annual tax return. Our records show that the following self-employment income was reported for you. Income Reported for You. Below is a table with 3 columns and 4 rows. Column headers are Self-Employment, Year, and Yearly Income. There are no row headers. Row 1 Self-Employment) /Type /Annot >>
endobj
